race.comment: DON'T RUSSIA (7) is going well for this and finds a suitable race after the scratching of the favourite. She found the line well at Sandown Hillside in a good BM66 last time out to grab third and has versatility which can see her land in a good spot from the low gate. Takes beating from there. GO TO HOLLYWOOD (5) doesn't win too many but hasn't been far away in small fields. Fresh for this and will be hard to hold out. OCTRAIN (3) resumes. He's not overly consistent but has pieces of form that would take some beating, setting up well from the low gate. DO IT NOW (9) wasn't far away last time and could sneak a placing.
